For a simple undirected graph with 3 vertices (labeled 1, 2, 3) connected in a triangle, the adjacency matrix A is a 3x3 matrix where A[i][j] = 1 if there is an edge between vertex i and vertex j, and 0 otherwise. The adjacency matrix is:

A = {
  {0, 1, 1},
  {1, 0, 1},
  {1, 1, 0}
}
